Roy Keane is poised to return to the Premier League - as Paul Lambert’s assistant at Aston Villa.

The former Manchester United midfielder turned the job as Celtic manager but is on the brink of a move to Villa Park.

Keane had been expected to be appointed as Neil Lennon’s successor at Parkhead after talks but the 42-year-old instead chose to work with Lambert, as the role would allow to also continue as Martin O’Neill’s No 2 with the Republic of Ireland. 

