Helping out: Shay Given (left) was promoted to a coaching role during Culverhouse's suspension

The FAI then released a short statement confirming Keane would remain with them after the recent frenzy of speculation over his future.

It read: ‘The Football Association of Ireland today confirmed that Roy Keane will travel with the Republic of Ireland squad to the US after he decided not to pursue the informal talks that took place with Celtic any further.’

Former West Bromwich Albion manager Steve Clarke is now the favourite for the Celtic job.

